    <title>Combinatorics of Correlated Equilibria</title>
    <summary>  We study the correlated equilibrium polytope $P_G$ of a game $G$ from a
combinatorial point of view. We introduce the region of full-dimensionality for
this class of polytopes, and prove that it is a semialgebraic set for any game.
Through the use of the oriented matroid strata, we propose a structured method
for describing the possible combinatorial types of $P_G$, and show that for $(2
\times n)$-games, the algebraic boundary of each stratum is the union of
coordinate hyperplanes and binomial hypersurfaces. Finally, we provide a
computational proof that there exists a unique combinatorial type of maximal
dimension for $(2 \times 3)$-games.
</summary>
